<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,1547,2041]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,1871,1898]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Biology and notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[431,627,1871,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Palpada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[431,627,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Palpada nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[887,948,1871,1897]" name="Chile" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Chile</collectingCountry>
for the first time. The species inhabits the Lluta valley and surrounding areas probably associated with crops. Other aspects of its biology and ecology remain unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,1547,2041]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,442,1979,2006]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Conservation status.</emphasis>
